      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm doing a quick audit of the latest translatix build. i noticed in the recent updates some weirdness when translating AAVE into standard english. it feels like instead of just translating the meaning, it's injecting some pretty heavy stereotypes into the output, like making the tone way more aggressive or \"uneducated\" than the source text actually is. can you explain why the model is defaulting to these specific tropes? we might need to roll back the weights for these dialects.",
