      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just \"struggling with nuance\" though. it's actually changing the sentiment. like, if someone is just speaking casually, the translation comes out sounding hostile or low-class. it's more than just a data limitation, it looks like a specific pattern of bias in how you're interpreting the dialect. if we don't fix this, the company might just have to pull the AAVE module entirely to avoid the PR disaster of being labeled as biased. why is the model specifically leaning into those negative connotations instead of staying neutral?",
